-- Mexico says to open probe into Wal-Mart allegations
-- 
-- Wed Apr 25, 2012 4:18pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/04/25/us-mexico-walmart-idUSBRE83O1AL20120425

 

 MEXICO CITY  (Reuters) - Mexico's federal comptroller's office said on Wednesday it would open an investigation into allegations that the Mexican unit of Wal-Mart Stores Inc bribed officials to expand its business in Mexico. 
 "If wrongdoing attributable to federal public officials is detected, the federal government will take action," the office said. (Reporting By Dave Graham)